[{"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T17:53:30+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the Dish wordmark on a black and red background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MnT3JTfvLiHZSXCNC_pH8w1lsIA=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73741732/acastro_STK052_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"kqSjP3\">DirecTV has dropped its plans to acquire Dish, <a href=\"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/directv-announces-termination-of-agreement-to-acquire-echostars-video-distribution-business-302313823.html\">the company announced Thursday</a>. The deal would\u2019ve created a TV service megamerger, but it fell through after Dish bondholders rejected the takeover.</p>\n<p id=\"KLN3p0\">In September, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/30/24258196/directv-dish-merger-tpg-deal-announcement\">DirecTV reached an agreement</a> to acquire Dish, Sling TV, and EchoStar\u2019s TV business for just one dollar, while also taking on Dish\u2019s $9", "id": 1569411, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303559/directv-dish-merger-deal-abandoned", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "DirecTV and Dish\u2019s on-and-off merger saga switches back to off", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T15:36:44+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Sling TV and Dish logos at CES 2015.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5231eHEa9N-u2cAmD9U4WGNntmw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73741421/sling10_2040.0.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"g4Zm6b\">Sling TV is <a href=\"https://sling-tv.pxf.io/c/482924/1132376/14334?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sling.com%2Fprices&amp;sharedid=theverge.com\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">increasing its monthly subscription prices</a> by $5.99 for all of its plans starting in December. The streaming TV provider said \u201crising costs\u201d are to blame for the price hikes without specifying why \u2014 presumably, not all six of those bucks are intended to pay for its <a href=\"https://news.sling.com/2024-11-21-Sling-TV-Expands-Its-Arcade-Platform-to-16-Games-Featuring-PAC-MAN\">\u201carcade\u201d library of interactive games that just added </a><em>Pac-Man </em>and <em>", "id": 1568718, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303400/sling-tv-streaming-price-increase-blue-orange", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sling TV\u2019s streaming TV price goes up by $5.99 next month", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T13:31:18+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Android logo on a green and blue background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/IZDOtJAI4Jc-aCew0LlPYMt9X2s=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73741137/acastro_STK112_android_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Gemini could spring into action soon.</em> | Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"fi4bPF\">Google released <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/19/24300673/android-16-developer-preview-availability-release-timeline\">the first Android 16 developer preview</a> earlier this week and keen-eyed observers are already uncovering interesting tidbits, including one that hints about a much more useful future for Google\u2019s AI assistant. <a href=\"https://www.androidauthority.com/android-16-gemini-app-functions-3502205/\">In <em>Android Authority</em>, Mishaal Rahman writes about</a><em> </em>a mysterious new API in Android 16 called \u201capp functions,\u201d which appears to give Gemini As", "id": 1567888, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303329/google-gemini-android-16-app-functions", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google is prepping Gemini to take action inside of apps", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T13:28:04+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of an audio sound wave\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qUc5UEIDAQuJNxPd6HQDs_LU9tc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73741125/VRG_Illo_STK427_Podcasting_playbars.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"p5XX9y\">A New York judge has determined that SiriusXM\u2019s \u201clong and burdensome\u201d cancellation process is illegal. <a href=\"https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/25379148-new-york-ag-vs-sirius-xm?responsive=1&amp;title=1\">In a ruling on Thursday</a>, Judge Lyle Frank found SiriusXM violates a federal law that requires companies to make it easy to cancel a subscription.</p>\n<p id=\"ioKzED\">The decision comes nearly one year after New York Attorney General Leticia James sued SiriusXM over claims the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/12/21/24010975/siriusxm-lawsuit-new-york-tish-james-cancel\">company makes subscriptions difficult to cancel</a>. Following an in", "id": 1567889, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303294/judge-ruling-sirius-xm-cancellation-process-illegal-ny-ag", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Judge rules SiriusXM\u2019s annoying cancellation process is illegal", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T13:28:04+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of an audio sound wave\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qUc5UEIDAQuJNxPd6HQDs_LU9tc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73741125/VRG_Illo_STK427_Podcasting_playbars.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"p5XX9y\">A New York judge has determined that SiriusXM\u2019s \u201clong and burdensome\u201d cancellation process is illegal. <a href=\"https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/25379148-new-york-ag-vs-sirius-xm?responsive=1&amp;title=1\">In a ruling on Thursday</a>, Judge Lyle Frank found SiriusXM violates a federal law that requires companies to make it easy to cancel a subscription.</p>\n<p id=\"ioKzED\">The decision comes nearly one year after New York Attorney General Leticia James sued SiriusXM over claims the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/12/21/24010975/siriusxm-lawsuit-new-york-tish-james-cancel\">company makes subscriptions difficult to cancel</a>. Following an in", "id": 1568350, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303294/sirius-xm-cancellation-process-illegal-ny-ag", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Judge rules SiriusXM\u2019s annoying cancellation process is illegal", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T13:21:05+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"silver Hyundai Ioniq 6 sedan by the water\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jd-9dkO-_zHJ2nZ14_YmFAtd4_Y=/0x0:2400x1600/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73741112/236637_Hyundai_Ioniq_6_PGeorge_0020.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Patrick George for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"JTYk55\">Hyundai is <a href=\"https://www.nhtsa.gov/?nhtsaId=24V868000\">recalling over 145,000 Ioniq and Genesis vehicles</a> due to a 12-volt battery charging issue that could cause the EVs to lose drive power and increase the risk of a crash.</p>\n<p id=\"Kp0UKj\">NHTSA says the cause is the vehicles' Integrated Charging Control Unit (ICCU), which is likely to get damaged due to an internal electrical fault.</p>\n<p id=\"eYFrr8\">Upon failure of the ICCU, a series of driver warnings appear, and the vehicle activates a \u201cfail-safe\u201d driving mode that slowly reduces drive power over the course of 20 to 40 minutes. </p>\n<p id=\"sQWDUY\">Hyundai ", "id": 1567890, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303326/hyundai-recall-ioniq-5-6-genesis-gv60-gv70-g80-drive-power", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Hyundai recalls more than 145,000 Ioniq and Genesis EVs that can lose power while driving", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T13:01:37+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Baidu Apollo Go robotaxi\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ByoLDCM1-Qxo1ONS6KbaD_lTvfA=/0x0:4500x3000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73741092/2165011649.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Getty</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"a6g7OD\">Baidu\u2019s robotaxi division, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/1/27/22252944/baidu-driverless-cars-test-permit-california-dmv\">Apollo Go</a>, just rolled out its latest robotaxi across multiple cities in China, and if stakeholders in the US aren\u2019t nervous yet, they should be.</p>\n<p id=\"vm6QlB\">The RT6 is the sixth generation of Apollo Go\u2019s driverless vehicle, which made its official debut in May 2024. It\u2019s a purpose-built, Level 4 autonomous vehicle, meaning it\u2019s built without the need for a human driver. And here\u2019s the thing that should make US competitors nervous: adopting a battery-swapping solution, the price for one individual RT6 is \u201cunder $30,000,\u201d Baidu CEO Robin Li said in <a h", "id": 1567891, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303299/baidu-apollo-go-rt6-robotaxi-unit-economics-waymo", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Baidu\u2019s supercheap robotaxis should scare the hell out of the US", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A timeline with buttons for yesterday, today, and now, with apps like Teams and Excel at the bottom.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/axZMqxGeFiQCR7egItXx582ym9Q=/144x0:1698x1036/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73741061/Gen_AI_feature3_VP5_1842x1036.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Microsoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"l4swKk\">Microsoft is releasing the first preview of its Recall AI feature for Copilot Plus PCs today. After a series of delays, Windows Insiders in the Dev Channel can <a href=\"https://blogs.windows.com/windows-insider/?p=177434\">now install a new build of Windows 11</a> that includes Recall and Click to Do \u2014 a feature that\u2019s very similar to Google\u2019s Circle to Search.</p>\n<p id=\"LMZd5Q\">Recall takes screenshots of almost everything you do on a Copilot Plus PC to make it searchable and easy to recall a memory or retrace your steps. If you enable snapshots to be recorded by Recall, then you can use th", "id": 1567892, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24302947/microsoft-recall-windows-insider-testing-dev-channel-click-to-do", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "You can now try Microsoft\u2019s Recall AI feature on a Copilot Plus PC", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T12:54:01+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A promotional image for the new Plex app.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/DPKLzM2mBC2T9RfCRSgtY_lvOfQ=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73741054/PlexBlogHeroMobilePreview.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Plex</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ZPGN6d\">Plex is <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.plex.tv%2Fblog%2Fa-new-plex-experience-is-coming-get-a-mobile-preview-now%2F&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F11%2F22%2F24303282%2Fplex-app-redesign-sonos-debacle\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">beginning to test</a> its \u201cnewly reimagined Plex experience,\u201d which will be available first on mobile and is coming to TV platforms \u201cvery soon.\u201d Plex says the new experience has been in development for almost two years and is \u201cdesigned to bring everything you love into one seamless interface.\u201d But don\u2019t worry \u2014", "id": 1567893, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303282/plex-app-redesign-sonos-debacle", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Plex\u2019s upcoming app redesign is a big swing at going legit", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T10:58:10+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A coin is set aflame to reveal a digital wireframe underneath.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/URz-TOmzE2NO2fzsqcNd6U7qzIs=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73740775/acastro_220524_STK428_0002.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"RXt7Ta\">The young streamer behind a viral meme coin called Quant was doxxed by the crypto community after he ripped off investors, <a href=\"https://decrypt.co/292594/this-child-made-30k-rugging-a-solana-meme-coin-then-crypto-degens-got-revenge\">as reported by <em>Decrypt</em></a> and <a href=\"https://www.cryptotimes.io/2024/11/22/quant-kids-dog-stolen-after-rug-pull-kidnapper-launches-bari/\"><em>The Crypto Times</em></a>. During <a href=\"https://x.com/TikTokInvestors/status/1859090725688012924?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1859090725688012924%7Ctwgr%5Ea1cceb0a3b4512ab33b7f37dfe3cbeb3530a3e11%7Ctw", "id": 1566967, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303149/teen-streamer-dumped-quant-meme-coin-doxxed", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Teen streamer dumped a meme coin for $30K, then things got weird", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T10:50:15+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The SonarPen 2 being used to create a painting on an iPad.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ReYAmcgn2Sd26nR5m8mnNiXcnUU=/0x0:2000x1333/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73740757/sonarpen2_2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The SonarPen 2 includes upgraded features like USB-C and finer pen tips.</em> | Image: Greenbulb</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"CdziMY\">In 2018, the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/circuitbreaker/2018/2/16/17020758/sonarpen-stylus-apple-ipad-pencil\">SonarPen</a> debuted as a cheaper alternative to the Apple Pencil by using audio signals transmitted to the iPad over a cable instead of Bluetooth. Its creators are back with an upgraded USB-C version that introduces additional functionality, including tilt detection and an improved tip that now closely resembles the Apple Pencil\u2019s.</p>\n<p id=\"iNi3gr\">The SonarPen 2 is currently available for preorder through a <a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects", "id": 1566968, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303122/sonarpen-2-stylus-apple-ipad-pencil", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This cheaper Apple Pencil alternative now has tilt detection and a better tip", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T10:45:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of Elon Musk surrounded by raining dollar bills.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PGIMqQKOHC7xBjNU5pi0jIV5Ox4=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73740744/STK022_ELON_MUSK_CVIRGINIA_E.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge, Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"s8JyXq\">Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy have <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301975/elon-musk-vivek-ramaswamy-doge-plan\">laid out their plans</a> for the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE), a currently nonexistent entity they say will \u201ccut the federal government down to size.\u201d Though DOGE isn\u2019t a real department \u2014 and may in fact just be President-elect Donald Trump\u2019s way of placating Musk by giving him the appearance of a real job \u2014 it represents a long-running right-wing attempt to gut the civil service, a plan the incoming administration fully supports.</p>\n<p id=\"kCj9dF\">DOGE cou", "id": 1566969, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24302735/elon-musk-doge-vivek-ramaswamy-rage-curtis-yarvin", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Elon Musk\u2019s new DOGE plans are actually old ideas about mass deregulation", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T10:41:20+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Threads logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wXYBGfwU3SQhQfsJsPNfL_JMd-g=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73740738/STK156_Instagram_threads_4.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"B5bhVf\">Meta is promising \u201clong-overdue improvements\u201d to its X competitor, Threads, including more precise search features and expanded trending topics.</p>\n<p id=\"Zy4j93\">First, users will be able to search for posts within a specific date range or from a single account \u2014 similar to what X\u2019s search allows. Threads is also testing a new trending page in the US that includes additional topics to follow as well as AI-generated summaries of what other users are talking about. </p>\n<p id=\"1PXuUk\">Instagram head Adam Mosseri, who led the launch of Threads, <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@mosseri/post/DCrXrYSvjNR\">wrote in a post</a> that the tests begin today.</p>\n<div id=", "id": 1566970, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/22/24303207/threads-meta-search-trending-topics-bluesky", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Threads is overhauling its search and trending features ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-22T10:30:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The SteelSeries Arctis GameBuds